Multi-units are used for prostheses supported by two or more screw-retained implants. Available in various versions: straight multi-units and angled multi-units 17 and 30 degrees with gingival heights from 1.5 to 4.5 mm.

description:

name: HELIX implant Ø 4.5
description:
The shape of all implants in a linear row along the length from the neck at a distance of 6 mm have exactly the same conical shape (in the section of one given diameter).
This provides us with the same strength throughout the entire linear range and the stability of clinical and physical parameters, regardless of the length of the used implant. During the Fatigue-test, the weak cross-section of all implants is measured at a distance of 3 mm from the implant neck, so we can safely say that the cross-section of all implants in diameter in a linear row is equally reliable and of equal strength.
Also, according to clinical studies, the main role in osseointegration is played by the first 6 mm of the implant length.
All implants are equipped with a cover screw
Length (L) refers to the length of the implant. The drills are marked 0.5 mm longer than the implant length, which corresponds to the principle of placing implants 0.5 mm below the cortical layer. Diameter (Ø) refers to the average diameter over the entire length of the implant.

name: BIA 5505
description:
The unique CROSSLOCK internal conical connection, with an angle of 15°, prevents the components from rolling, loosens the screw and provides reliable long-term stability and optimized load distribution. And thanks to the conical design of the implant body and the deep characteristic faces of the thread, it was possible to increase the area of ​​contact of the implant with the bone, and hence a high level of primary stability.
ASPER is made of hypoallergenic titanium Grade 4 Nano - a material that, according to mechanical tests, showed a higher level of strength compared to titanium of the 4th class and has no alternative impurities in its composition. The pronounced osteoconductivity and mechanical strength of the material are complemented by the parameters of the SLA Pro coating. This is the optimal microtexture of the surface, thanks to which it acquires an ideal topography for cell attachment, and thus creates the conditions for a full and successful process of osseointegration.
The ASPER implant, like other products from TM Bauer's Implants, has a lifetime warranty and is protected by a personal identification code and security marking. Functional stability and safety of Bauer's Implants products are confirmed in accordance with the international standard ISO 14801 "Dentistry - Implants - Dynamic fatigue test for endosseous dental implants".
All implants are equipped with a screw cap.
